						               													<description>Rikiki et le tr&amp;eacute;sor de Barbe-Noire is a cooperative course game. It is inspired from a children book character created by Marianne Barcilon. The players must collect all the treasures before the Pirate Blackbeard rebuilds his ship and catches them.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In his turn, the player rolls the dice and applies the result among:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     arrows: the front player has as many squares as there are arrows.&amp;#10;     the compass rose: the player draws an action card and applies its effect&amp;#10;     Pirate Flag: The player draws a piece from Blackbeard's ship and begins to assemble it.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When a player stops on a treasure map, he collects one of the tokens there. If the token is the seagull that lays the golden eggs, it collects all the tokens present there.&amp;#10;The action cards allow you to replay, go back, move forward several spaces or even remove a piece from Blackbeard's boat.&amp;#10;The game ends when Blackbeard's boat is completed, the players have lost OR when all the treasure tokens have been collected, the players have won.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
